Differentiate var, let, const:

var, let, const is a variable declaration keyword.

Before the advent of ES6 using popular keyword is var.

After the advent of ES6 using keyword is let and const.

var:

var variable declarations are two types : global variable and local variable

The variable declared in outside a function it’s called global variable

The variable declared in inside a function it’s called local variable

var variables can be re-declared and updated.

var variables are declared before executing the value of return is undefined.

If it uses the re-declare variable in the different block, it will throw errors.

var variables can be declared without being initialized

let:

let variables are block-scoped

A block is a chunk of code bounded by {}.

A block lives in curly braces. Anything within curly braces is a block.

let variables can be accessed at block level only

let variables can be updated but not re-declared.

let variables are declared before executing the value of return is Reference Error.

let variables can be declared without being initialized

const

const variables are block-scoped

object also declared in const

const variables must be initialized during declaration.

const object cannot be updated, the properties of this objects can be updated.

const variables cannot be updated or re-declared

const variables are declared before executing the value of return is Reference Error.
